1 unit(s) Tofu
1 tbsp BBQ Seasoning
113 g Corn Kernels
4 tbsp Ranch Dressing
350 g Yellow Potato
1 tsp Garlic Salt
1 unit(s) Green Onion
1 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
2 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch thick rounds.
Add potatoes and 1 tbsp oil to an unlined baking sheet. (NOTE: For 4 ppl, use 2 baking sheets, with 1 tbsp oil per sheet.) Season with 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) garlic salt and pepper, then toss to coat.
Roast in the top of the oven until tender, 24-25 min.

While potatoes roast, pat tofu dry with paper towels. Cut tofu in half, parallel to the cutting board. (NOTE: You will have two square tofu steaks per block.) Using a fork, poke tofu all over.
Combine tofu, BBQ seasoning, 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) garlic salt and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil in a medium bowl. Toss to coat.
Arrange tofu in a single layer on another unlined baking sheet.
Roast in the middle of the oven, flipping halfway through, until tender and golden, 8-10 min.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium heat.
When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter, then swirl the pan until melted, 1 min.
Add corn and 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) water. Stir to combine. Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, 5-6 min. Season with salt and pepper.

Meanwhile, thinly slice green onion.
In a small bowl, stir together ranch and half the green onions. Season with salt and pepper.

Slice tofu.
Divide tofu, corn and potatoes between plates.
Drizzle some ranch dressing over corn, then sprinkle with remaining green onions.
Serve with remaining ranch dressing on the side.

If you've opted to get tofu, pat tofu dry with paper towels. Cut tofu in half, parallel to the cutting board. (NOTE: You will have two square tofu steaks per block.) Using a fork, poke tofu all over. Season tofu in the same way the recipe instructs you to season the chicken breasts. Roast in the middle of the oven, flipping halfway through, until tender and golden, 8-10 min.

Plate tofu in the same way the recipe instructs you to plate the chicken breasts.